      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>A professor of English at Leicester University in Great Britain, George Fraser was the advisor of Mark Jacobs, whose dissertation examined the poetry of American author and critic Laura (Riding) Jackson.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Photocopies of correspondence, mainly from Laura (Riding) Jackson to George Fraser, in which they discuss Jacob's work as well as each other's literary work and other authors, including Robert Graves, James Reeves, and Norman Cameron.</p>
      </scopecontent>
